The introduction of the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.gulfweb.org/bigdoc/report/riegle1.html">Riegle report</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> refers to Congressional hearings at which this was established, though I have not yet tracked down a record of these hearings.  (For the interested, it also chronicles the <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.gulfweb.org/bigdoc/report/r_1_2.html#exports">export of biological materials</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> to Iraq before the Gulf War.)<br>
Nandarie:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Let's  not  forget  that  France  has huge business interests in Iraq, which would be upset due to war. What country refines/etc over half of Iraq's oil? France.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
This is true; I will even <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.globalpolicy.org/security/oil/2002/0919threats.htm">provide a link</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> in defense of your statement.  But do note:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Last year, France ranked No. 1 among European countries doing business with Iraq, with $1.5 billion in trade, followed by Italy, with $1 billion.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
(This $1.5b is private industry, mainly oil companies.) <br>
However!  The US has already started planning the reconstruction of Iraq, and is awarding the construction contracts to American companies -- <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.tampatribune.com/MGAON33JCDD.html">contracts that will run into the billions of dollars</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.  eg:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Contracts could be awarded within two weeks. Just one of eight contracts alone - a U.S. Agency for International Development request for highway and other ``capital construction'' by several behemoth construction firms - is expected quickly to consume $1 billion.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I don't know the size of the other contracts (this too may be on the web somewhere), and assuming 8 x $1b seems simplistic -- but it doesn't seem unreasonable to assume that the combined worth will exceed France's $1.5b, possibly even the $2.5b of France and Italy combined.  In short: the cleanup effort alone will pour billions into American industry, to speak nothing of the cost of war itself.<br>
I don't like the claim that this is a war for oil, since I don't believe it's true; the motivation for conflict in this case seems far more complex (and possibly more sinister, but I will save that for later).  But conversely, to deny that there are people -- both inside and outside the government -- who believe that the war is an essential remedy for the American economy is solipsistic.  (Personally, I find the concept of war as a massive pork-barrel project so cynical that it numbs the mind, zen koan-style; that does not change the fact that I know people who work on and around Wall Street who believe it.)<br>
To wrap up: I have no problem with condemning France's attempts to protect its own business interests -- its self-serving and ultimately counter-productive to global stability.  But realize also that America's business interest in war is greater than France's business interest in peace.  Any credible strategy for long-term peace will have to address both of these problems.<br>
Time for that second cup of coffee. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub27.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=morloc>Morloc</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:blue;'>Tavern Regular</span></span><br>  Posts: 489<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(3/18/03 11:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntavernthefurnace.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3174.topic&index=59>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.mindspring.com/~lnalewajk/_images/Scrimm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: facts</span><hr size=1> <br>
